Subject: rPSA-2008-0082-1 espgs

rPath Security Advisory: 2008-0082-1
Published: 2008-02-28
Products:
    rPath Linux 1

Rating: Major
Exposure Level Classification:
    Indirect User Deterministic Unauthorized Access
Updated Versions:
    espgs=conary.rpath.com@rpl:1/8.15.1-1.5-1

rPath Issue Tracking System:
    https://issues.rpath.com/browse/RPL-2217

References:
    http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2008-0411

Description:
    Previous versions of the espgs package are vulnerable to an Arbitrary
    Code Execution attack in which an attacker may use a maliciously crafted
    PostScript file to trigger a buffer overflow.

http://wiki.rpath.com/Advisories:rPSA-2008-0082

